        "timestamp": 1654638147
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and perhaps this:<br>\n<a href=\"https://acp.copernicus.org/articles/9/2577/2009/acp-9-2577-2009.pdf\">https://acp.copernicus.org/articles/9/2577/2009/acp-9-2577-2009.pdf</a></p>",
        "id": 56156,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Long",
        "timestamp": 1654640193
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here's an application of particle advection to the \"RunningTide\" approach to CDR (launching free-drifting algae platforms)<br>\n<a href=\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41559-022-01722-1\">https://www.nature.com/articles/s41559-022-01722-1</a></p>",
        "id": 56599,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Long",
        "timestamp": 1655225820
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There's some relationship between our questions and \"finite-time Lyapunov exponents,\" which provide a scalar representation of spreading rate. I am not sure how useful FTLE's are in the context of the problem at hand...but they might be and there's substantial literature exploring their applications.</p>",
        "id": 56618,
